            "kind": "text",
            "ranges": [
              {
                "kind": "range",
                "text": ". In an alienated world, the value of developing social bonds and an expanded social life shouldn't be underestimated. \nVolunteering helps people manage and lower stress levels. Helping others, our body releases oxytocin, which buffers stress. \nPerspective – working with others can help us re-examine and reflect on our own lives. \n",
                "marks": []
              }
            ]
          },
