                "text": "focused on people over the age of 50 found that after a year of volunteering they all felt greater self esteem, personal growth, and a sense of being productive. The research found that volunteers were more likely to feel such things when given adequate training and flexibility in choosing a schedule.  \nFeeling like you have more time – like those who give to charity often feeling wealthier, Cassie Mogilner's research found that people feel less ",
