          {
            "kind": "text",
            "ranges": [
              {
                "kind": "range",
                "text": ", 62.6 million people volunteered through an organization at least once from September 2014- 2015. Women volunteered at a higher rate than men. 35-54 year-olds were the most likely to volunteer. Married and white people also volunteered at high rates. It appears that stability and poverty levels play a role in people's desire or ability to volunteer. The average amount of volunteering was 1 hour per week. Religious organisations were the main places people volunteered, followed by educational and youth services. \nAccording to the Charities Aid Foundation, at a ",
                "marks": []
